State of the Media Research Nation

MRG | Culture of Insight

Nov 2018

About this survey

The theme of the 2018 Media Research Group (MRG) Conference is “Reflections”, which seemed like a good opportunity to take a look at the state of the Media Research industry, in the eyes of its practitioners. Members of the MRG were asked to complete a short online survey covering questions such as:-

  • how their jobs have changed
  • whether they spend enough time on the tasks that matter
  • attendance at industry events
  • their relationships with their clients or suppliers
  • areas for improvement in the industry’s outlook
  • skills that the industry may need more of, and
  • potential candidates for “Year Of” in 2019…

This report charts the 100 partial and complete responses to the survey.

Respondent Profiles

There were 100 respondents to the survey.

Company Activity

The respondent sample broke down as follows:- Client-side companies: 38; Ad-hoc research suppliers: 35; Research product suppliers: 27

Seniority Level

The respondent sample broke down as follows:- Execs/senior execs: 9; Managers/ADs: 20; Directors/Heads: 32; MD/CEO/Board: 14; Company owners: 11
